name: John Tognela Rest Area
directions: Pull off the Forrest Highway.   The rest area is well signposted.
comment:
Lots of free untimed parking;  you can camp for 24 hours.   The  water is not drinkable. 

Gendered single occupant stalls,  all with extra room and grabrails.     Basins outside the stalls,  undercover.   Doors open inwards,  doors and locks are manual.   

Concrete paths from paved parking area, no designated accessible parking.   

Area and toilets lit at night.   Available 24/7.
